  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance and Admin Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Financial Management &amp; Reporting</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage the full-cycle accounting process, including general ledger maintenance, accounts payable, accounts receivable, and fixed assets.</li>\n  <li>Prepare monthly and annual financial statements in compliance with relevant accounting standards. With hands-on experience in month end activities.</li>\n  <li>Assist in the annual budgeting and forecasting process.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Compliance &amp; Internal Controls</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ensure adherence to all local, state, and federal financial regulations and tax requirements.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and support audits, serving as a primary point of contact and preparing necessary documentation.</li>\n  <li>Maintain and improve internal financial controls and accounting policies to safeguard company assets and ensure data integrity.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Operational and Admin Support</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Process and manage employee expense reports accurately and on time.</li>\n  <li>Reconcile bank statements and financial discrepancies on a regular basis.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with other departments to provide financial insights for operational decision-making.</li>\n  <li>Perform other tasks as assigned, supporting various divisions and initiatives when required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>Diploma or Bachelor's degree or equivalent, with a minimum of 1 year of experience in accounting.</li>\n  <li>Strong organizational skills with the ability to manage time effectively.</li>\n  <li>Good communication skills, with the ability to collaborate as a team player and work independently.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in MS Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint).</li>\n  <li>Experience or proficiency in accounting software (Quickbooks or Xero) will be an added advantage.</li>\n</ol>",
